## WHY "UL FOR AI"? THE ANALOGY

**Underwriters Laboratories (UL)** doesn't build toasters. They test toasters. They stress-test them against fire, shock, and material failure. When you see the UL certification mark, you know the product won't burn your house down.

We do the same thing for AI agents:
- We don't build the AI agent. The enterprise brings their own agent (GPT-4o, Claude, Llama, Gemini, custom fine-tune).
- We **stress-test it** against realistic, adversarial tool-integration scenarios across 38+ MCP servers (Stripe, Jira, Epic FHIR, Salesforce, Plaid, GitLab, etc.).
- We issue a **certification report** that says: "This agent passed 94% of multi-hop reasoning tasks, failed 100% of temporal logic traps, and has a 23% silent failure rate on chained API mutations."

**The customer is NOT OpenAI or Anthropic.** The customer is the enterprise deploying THEIR agents into production workflows — the healthcare system connecting GPT to their EHR, the fintech connecting Claude to their payment APIs, the legal firm connecting Gemini to their document management system.

