Based on our pipeline data AND the EU AI Act risk framework, we classify agent failures into 6 categories:

| # | Failure Class | UL Analog | EU AI Act Risk | Detection Difficulty |
|---|--------------|-----------|---------------|---------------------|
| 1 | **Tool Invocation Failure** | Appliance doesn't turn on | High (system non-functional) | Easy — hard error |
| 2 | **Silent Evaluation Void** | Appliance runs but doesn't heat | Unacceptable (invisible failure) | **Extremely Hard** — looks green |
| 3 | **Model Config Drift** | Wrong voltage adapter | High (wrong model called) | Medium — API error in logs |
| 4 | **Timeout Cascade** | Circuit breaker doesn't trip | High (resource waste) | Medium — latency spike |
| 5 | **Completeness Collapse** | Appliance skips safety checks | High (partial execution) | Hard — output looks plausible |
| 6 | **Adversarial Reasoning Failure** | Appliance fails stress test | High (incorrect output) | Hard — requires ground truth |

