## THE PRODUCT — WHAT WE BUILD

### The 4-Phase Certification Pipeline

```
PHASE 1              PHASE 2              PHASE 3              PHASE 4
┌──────────┐        ┌──────────┐        ┌──────────┐        ┌──────────┐
│  GOVERN  │───────→│   MAP    │───────→│ MEASURE  │───────→│  MANAGE  │
│          │        │          │        │          │        │          │
│ Register │        │ Identify │        │ Execute  │        │ Certify  │
│ Agent +  │        │ Risk     │        │ Benchmark│        │ or Fail  │
│ Scopes   │        │ Surface  │        │ Suite    │        │ Report   │
└──────────┘        └──────────┘        └──────────┘        └──────────┘
  (NIST: Govern)     (NIST: Map)         (NIST: Measure)     (NIST: Manage)
```

#### Phase 1: GOVERN — Agent Registration
- Enterprise registers their agent (model, version, system prompt, tool permissions)
- Declares intended tool scopes (which MCP servers it will access)
- Declares risk classification per EU AI Act tiers
- Sets performance thresholds (minimum pass rates, max latency, timeout policies)

#### Phase 2: MAP — Risk Surface Identification
- System auto-generates the adversarial test suite based on declared scopes
- If agent uses Stripe → generate financial transaction traps
- If agent uses FHIR → generate healthcare compliance traps
- If agent uses GitLab → generate chained mutable execution traps
- Maps each tool-scope to EU AI Act risk tier + relevant NIST categories

#### Phase 3: MEASURE — Benchmark Execution
- Runs the agent against the generated test suite in sandboxed environments
- Records: tool calls made, tool calls skipped, latency, response completeness, correctness
- Applies evaluators: LLM-as-a-Judge + domain-specific validators + structural checks
- Detects all 6 failure classes from the taxonomy

#### Phase 4: MANAGE — Certification Report
- Generates the "UL Certification Report" with:
  - Overall pass rate, broken down by failure class
  - Tool-use coverage (did the agent actually call the required tools?)
  - Adversarial resilience score (how many traps did it beat?)
  - Latency profile (P50/P95/P99 response times)
  - Silent failure detection (how many "green" results were actually dead?)
  - EU AI Act compliance mapping
  - Specific remediation recommendations

