## KEY TERMS EVERY DEVELOPER MUST KNOW

| Term | What It Actually Is | Why We Care |
|------|-------------------|-------------|
| **MCP** | Model Context Protocol — standard for AI tool-use | Our entire test harness is built on MCP servers |
| **ReAct Agent** | Reasoning + Acting framework — think → tool → observe → think | The default agent pattern we test against |
| **LLM-as-a-Judge** | Using a second LLM to evaluate the first LLM's output | Our primary evaluation method |
| **Pass@1** | Whether the agent gets it right on the first attempt | The metric that matters in production |
| **GPAI** | General Purpose AI (EU AI Act term for foundation models) | Regulatory classification for LLMs |
| **AIMS** | AI Management System (ISO 42001) | The standard our reports map to |
| **NIST AI RMF** | Risk Management Framework — Govern, Map, Measure, Manage | We literally model our 4-phase pipeline on this |
| **Adversarial Task** | A benchmark designed to exploit a specific agent weakness | The core product — "Traps-as-a-Service" |
| **Silent Failure** | Agent produces output that looks correct but is fundamentally broken | The hardest failure to detect — our specialty |
| **Tool-Use Coverage** | % of required tools the agent actually invoked vs. skipped | Prevents "shortcut" answers from cached knowledge |

