### 10.5 The Cookbook-Grounded Evaluator Taxonomy (Final State)

After integrating all Tier 1 steals, our evaluator registry supports:

```
EVALUATION_FUNCTIONS:
  "json"          → Parse JSON from agent output         [T1: code]
  "get"           → Extract key from parsed JSON          [T1: code]
  "len"           → Count items in a list                 [T1: code]
  "raw"           → Pass raw string to comparison         [T1: code]
  "llm_judge"     → Claude-as-judge (NEW - Tier 1 steal)  [T3: model]

COMPARISON_FUNCTIONS:
  "="             → Exact match                           [T1: code]
  "<", "<=", ">",">=", "in", "contain"  → Standard ops  [T1: code]

DOMAIN EVALUATORS (per-domain, loaded dynamically):
  "grant_application.*"   → IRB timeline, budget, narrative validators
  "web_search.*"          → Source verification, multi-hop chain
  "governance_traps.*"    → 4 Pillar custom evaluators (llm_judge-backed)
```

Every new domain we add gets its own evaluators. Every complex evaluation uses `llm_judge`. Every simple structural check uses code. This is the Anthropic-endorsed architecture for production eval systems.

